this is an update about my relationship.

it’s not owed to anyone, but it is something that I’ve been wanting to put into the open because intentionally avoiding it has been tiresome. I’ve also just haven’t been ready to talk about it, but I am now.

so. after nearly 14 years of being together, me and my partner @jonathanmead decided at the beginning of this year to put intentional physical distance between us. we are living apart—together.

it's a very long, complicated story, and I've decided to share this story on my podcast, @sexuallyliberatedwoman—not just because I enjoy podcasting, but because my podcast is where I go to speak about my own journey of healing and liberation in the realms of sex, relationships, and my own identity. so it just feels right to talk about my “separation" there. (you can listen to ep. 48 of The Sexually Liberated Woman on Apple Podcasts, Spotify, Stitcher, etc. just for it or click the link in my bio.) this has challenged us both deeply—yet, there is still so much love between us. and we both have already seen how transitioning our relationship in this way has given us space to honor our individual freedom while creating new ways to stay connected with each other.

this relationship continues to be a safe space for me to be the entire truth of myself, and I’m so grateful to be supported with a love that allows me to stay free.

i love you, jonathan.

@evyan.whitney thank you for sharing ! My bf and I recently moved in together and we have separate rooms, which some think is weird (whatever that means 🤷🏻‍♀️). It wonderful to see that there is no normal to a relationship. The people in that relationship need to do what is right for them, not what society tells us we need to do. Keep on doing you! ❤️❤️❤️
i love this so much. all of this.
@transpirationalhealer

My partner and I decided to do the same thing last year when I moved back to my hometown after being together for 6 years and living together for 4 of them. It’s been THE BEST thing that we’ve ever done for our relationship. Congratulations!!!
You’re now dating Kevyn Aucoin?
Ahhh I'm so happy for you both, that you've found a new way to be together, while honouring your other individual needs/ desires. So much love coming your way 💜

Just finished the podcast! Firstly, I love hearing your soothing and sweet voice 😌 it’s been a while. And second, it really sparked such an important conversation for my partner and I around ultimate freedom and how much do we allow to just die within ourselves because fighting for it was harder than just giving up on the need for whatever the freedom was. I think of my mother who has sacrificed the last 26 years living in the suburbs when she deeply wants to move to NW Portland, but she allows that dream to simply die within her because advocating for herself feels too hard. Easier to allow her husband to have what he wants; a suburban life. Anyways, your pod applies to so many different aspects of life and I’m also jazzed to learn a new term (LAT)!
thank you for this 💕 sharing your experiences makes for incredible source of knowledge and inspiration
Thankyou for talking about this 💗
Thank you for sharing your story. I’m so happy for you that you’ve chosen to prioritize your self! It takes so much courage to take that leap. I’m excited for your journeys together - apart.

i haven’t even listened to your podcast yet, but have in recent times been trying to negotiate my own desire to be in intentional relationship, but also considering that living with my partner may take away from the individuality we celebrate. just seeing that there is consideration elsewhere in the world along these lines give me some release to continue to follow my intuition on this. thank you for sharing and for showing up in the world in the way you do.

thank you for sharing this, i’m grateful to encounter pages like your whet you can find very relatable experiences or just an insight to life which can help others guide through theirs. i appreciate you ❤️

Loved loved loved reading your transcript. Felt like I was reading a heartfelt letter from an old friend. Thank you so much for providing a transcript too - this is rare, much to the frustration of deaf folks. Thank you again for sharing your story - it’s soul fillin’ stuff ❤️
it means so much for you to be candid and fearless in this way, especially as a black woman ❤️ thanks ev’yan🥰
Mmm those kisses💗
Thank you for sharing. I enjoyed hearing about different types of relationships
I’m so happy you shared this.. my heart really needed to hear your story 💙
Thank you so much for sharing this! It’s an honor to witness 💗🌸
Loved this! Thanks for sharing!

Thank you for sharing this! It’s funny cause I was in a long distance relationship with someone in on a whole other continent, and to be honest with the help of FaceTime and WhatsApp, it really helped us to better understand each other. It was difficult at first, but I think it helped us to put so much more value into our relationships.
